<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 945
                    The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations (
                        Pauley
                    ) to the Assistant Secretary of State
                        (
                        Clayton
                    )Printed from a carbon copy on which
                        there is an uncertified typed signature.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d945</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">945</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-29T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="945" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d945">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> Files</note>
                <head>No. 945<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pauley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_CWL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clayton</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d945fn1">Printed from a carbon copy on which
                        there is an uncertified typed signature.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-29">July 29,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CWL1">Clayton</persName>
                    </hi>: I have your memorandum of July 28<note n="2" xml:id="d945fn2">
                        <ref target="#d944">document No. 944</ref>.</note> suggesting that we might
                    concur in the recommendation concerning certain questions regarding restitution
                    of art objects, as recommended by the Headquarters, U. S. Group Control
                    Council.</p>
                <p>At your suggestion I have prepared a joint memorandum<note n="3" xml:id="d945fn3">Enclosure to <ref target="#d964">document No. 964</ref>.</note> and have
                    indicated my approval of it by my signature thereon. If it meets with your
                    approval I presume you will transmit the same to <persName corresp="#p_CLGLD1">General Clay</persName> for appropriate action.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin W. Pauley</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
